textBeforeTable: Tuesday, April 30, 2013 Meet Results By Division – Boys Bluegrass Conference Meet It was Lamoni that dominated their home track and ended up sweeping the Co-ed Bluegrass Conference meet on Tuesday night. Lamoni’s girls had 145 points, and second place went to Twin Cedars who had 110, and Melcher-Dallas was third with 90. The Saints’ girls finished first in the 1500 meter run, as Hannah Wilson crossed the line with a time of just over 6:07. Melcher-Dallas’ 1600 meter medley relay team also came in first. For Twin Cedars, a pair of wins by Brittney Roby in the 800 meter run and 100 meter hurdles highlighted their evening, as well as first place in the 800 meter medley relay. On the boys’ side, Melcher-Dallas was third and the Sabers finished fourth in a meet dominated by both Lamoni and Murray, who combined for 345 points. Cody Alexander for the Saints was first in the 400 meter dash, with a once-around time of 52.66. The Sabers were second in the 4 x 100 meter relay. A full list of results can be found below.
